<HEADLINE>
USC RIGHT ON SCHEDULE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC conducted its first official scrimmage Friday
evening, although it was the second-string players who played most
of the key roles.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans were without six players _ including starting wide
receivers Kareem Kelly and Marcell Allmond and tailback Sultan
McCullough _ who were preparing for today's Centennial Invitational
track meet at USC.
</P>
<P>
   That gave several other skill players a chance, and walk-on wide
receiver Matt Nickels made the most of his opportunity, with three
receptions for 63 yards in the 50-play scrimmage at Howard Jones
Field. Fullback Chad Pierson scored the only touchdown on a 47-yard
run.
</P>
<P>
   Kicker David Bell made two of five field goals, converting from
40 and 39 yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``We didn't have a lot of our guys, so it didn't go the way we
wanted,'' said quarterback Carson Palmer. ``At times we looked good
and at times shaky.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmer completed four of nine passes for 28 yards and Mike Van
Raaphorst completed nine of 16 passes for 104 yards. Tailback
Malaefou MacKenzie had 25 yards in eight carries; Pierson finished
with 52 yards in two carries.
</P>
<P>
   `` The intention today was to give guys an opportunity,'' USC
coach Paul Hackett said. ``Matt Nickels made a move today for a
scholarship. I feel we're about where I thought we'd be at the
halfway mark. Now we have to make a move.''
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans had eight penalties, three less than in last week's
controlled scrimmage. Offensive lineman Brent McCaffrey sprained
his ankle during the scrimmage and his status next week is
questionable.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive end Shamsud-Din Abdul-Shaheed, who hurt his shoulder
earlier in the week, will undergo surgery on Tuesday and miss the
remainder of spring practice. It's also likely offensive lineman
Lucais MacKay will skip the rest of practice to concentrate on
track.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-01-00 0155EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
