   Top center story:
</P>
<P>
   GIFTS-TAX-DODGE (Undated) _ To save on taxes, Americans
routinely understate the value of what they give their heirs,
particularly stock in family-owned businesses and real estate, new
data from the Internal Revenue Service shows. But the agency has
almost no resources to stop the problem, and a recently passed law
has only increased the chances of not getting caught. By David Cay
Johnston.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 2 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   ACHING-HEARTLAND (Tryon, Neb.) _ While most of the American
economy is going gangbusters, many rural areas are undergoing a
wrenching restructuring that is impoverishing small ranchers and
farmers, depopulating large chunks of rural America and changing
the way Americans get their food. The gains in farming and ranching
efficiency are staggering, but so too is the blow to the rural way
of life. A special report. By Nicholas D. Kristof.
</P>
<P>
   With photos and map.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 2 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
