<P>
   COPTER-DEBATE (Burbank, Calif.) _ Television stations tout the
value of helicopters in reaching news events quickly, with a
perspective impossible for land-bound reporters. But critics point
out chopper coverage often sensationalizes minor events and
trivializes the news itself - all to justify the thousands of
dollars spent keeping L.A.'s TV fleet of a dozen ``telecopters''
aloft every day. By Harrison Sheppard. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BIG-MURAL (Los Angeles) _ The world's longest mural - a Los
Angeles landmark located in the San Fernando Valley - is fading
fast after 25 years of sun, rain and earthquakes. Dismayed by the
city's neglect of this important artwork, the artists who painted
it over six summers starting in 1975 now are launching an ambitious
plan to restore the Great Wall of Los Angeles. By Dominic Berbeo.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
